description: Recently sold: $170,000. BACK ON THE MARKET.  Buyers financing fell thru! Inspections done - ready to go! FHA appraisal is complete and is higher than list price! Instant equity! Lovingly cared for w attention to detail is prevalent throughout.  Bright kitchen w plenty of cabinetry & cupboards.  Just beyond that is the arch way into the bright dining room.  The living room has gleaming original hardwood floors & masterfully crafted woodwork on the walls.  Original light fixtures & brand new french doors.  One set of doors leads to the freshly painted deck, the other to the covered & enclosed front porch w bead board ceilings as well.  Mn flr bdrm, lg full bath.  Wooden stairs bring you up to the lg open rm which one can easily add a closet for a full fledged bedroom.  Built ins and shelving already in place.  Basement is old school, but remains dry & clean.  Laundry & walk in shower. Newer water htr, furnace & a/c. Newer roof. New patio doors.  Gardeners paradise.  Arguably the cutest house in North Branch!

description:
For sale: $377,500. WHY BUILD WHEN ALL DONE FOR LESS!!

Built by current owners with loads of upgrades & improvements since.  Continuous pressure well pump, granite counters & top-of-the-line KitchenAid appliances are just a few of them. 

Entire basement finished with BR, bath, and family room with fireplace. Numerous improvements outside as well including upgraded concrete drive and walk, hardscape, and irrigation system.  Room left for outbuilding which would have been the next project along with final touches to landscaping.


This is a home with good use of space that is perfect for your growing family and/or entertaining. Spacious main floor boasts functional kitchen with 2  dining areas.  Other features include 4 BR's on one level, 2 good sized living areas, on demand water heater, and a 3 car garage that is completely finished, insulated & heated. 

Located minutes from DT North Branch, loads of shopping/restaurants, and Hwy. 35 while retaining that country feel gives this the best of both worlds!
Recently sold: $135,000.
